# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout for every platform.
#
# Why this matters here: Playwright's text snapshots (and the
# JSON.stringify output the payload-snapshot test compares against) always
# use LF. Without this file, git's autocrlf on Windows rewrites checked-out
# files to CRLF, so the byte-level snapshot comparison fails with a diff
# that shows no visible difference (every line differs only by a trailing
# \r). Pinning eol=lf makes the working tree deterministic everywhere.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders: the snapshot fixtures must never be CRLF.
tests/**/*.json text eol=lf
